#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "JLink packaging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "<a class=\"status-label status-experimental\" title=\"This extension requests early feedback to mature the idea\" href=\"#extension-status-note\">experimental</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"The `jlink` extension produces a custom Java runtime image for a Quarkus application.\n"
"The image contains only the JDK modules and application modules that are needed to run the application, resulting in a smaller, faster, and more self-contained distribution.\n"
"This extension depends on the xref:modularity.adoc[Quarkus modularity extension] to compute the application's module graph."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"The `jlink` extension requires Java 25 or later.\n"
"Earlier JDK versions have compatibility issues with the `jlink` tool that prevent reliable image generation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"Add the `quarkus-jlink` extension to your project.\n"
"When the extension is present, a `jlink` image is produced automatically as part of the normal Quarkus build.\n"
"JAR packaging is disabled when `jlink` is active."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "After adding the extension, build the project normally:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "The `jlink` image is written to the output directory (by default, `target/jlink-output/image`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Running the image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "To run the application, execute the launcher script in the image's `bin` directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"The launcher name currently defaults to `my-app`.\n"
"A future release will derive the default from `quarkus.package.output-name`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Image layout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"The output directory has the standard `jlink` image structure.\n"
"The `bin/` directory contains the launcher script.\n"
"The `lib/` directory contains the JDK runtime modules.\n"
"Application modules that are not on the boot module path are placed in `lib/quarkus/` and are loaded dynamically on demand after startup by `smallrye-modules`.\n"
"See the xref:modularity.adoc[modularity guide] for an explanation of boot modules and dynamic modules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Configuration reference"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "<span class=\"icon\"><i class=\"fa fa-lock\" title=\"Fixed at build time\"></i></span> Configuration property fixed at build time - All other configuration properties are overridable at runtime <input type=\"search\" id=\"config-search-0\" placeholder=\"FILTER CONFIGURATION\" disabled>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "CDS support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid "Support for Class Data Sharing (CDS) and AOT precompilation within jlink images is planned for a future release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/jlink.adoc
msgid ""
"CDS currently only applies to modules on the boot module path.\n"
"Dynamic modules loaded by `smallrye-modules` are not eligible for CDS precompilation at this time."
msgstr ""
